# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.example — copy to `.env` for local dev and fill with REAL values.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# NEVER commit `.env`. It is gitignored. In production these live ONLY as
# Vercel Environment Variables (Project → Settings → Environment Variables).
#
# Legend:
#   [server-only]  Secret. Must NOT be exposed to the browser. Only read
#                  inside /api serverless functions and /lib (server code).
#   [public]       Safe to expose to the browser. (None are prefixed VITE_
#                  yet — add that prefix only to vars you intentionally want
#                  bundled into the frontend.)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── WHOOP OAuth ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# From the WHOOP Developer Dashboard (https://developer.whoop.com) → your app.

# [public]  OAuth client identifier for your WHOOP app.
WHOOP_CLIENT_ID=your-whoop-client-id

# [server-only]  OAuth client secret. Used only in /api to exchange the auth
# code for tokens and to refresh tokens. Never send this to the browser.
WHOOP_CLIENT_SECRET=your-whoop-client-secret

# [server-only-ish]  The redirect/callback URL registered in the WHOOP
# dashboard. Must match the registered value EXACTLY. ROADMAP Phase 1 uses the
# `/api/callback` serverless route — confirm the final path when you build auth.
#   Local:       http://localhost:3000/api/callback
#   Production:   https://<your-app>.vercel.app/api/callback
WHOOP_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/callback

# ── Supabase ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# From Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API.

# [public]  Project URL, e.g. https://abcdefgh.supabase.co
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co

# [server-only]  Service role key. FULL admin access, bypasses Row Level
# Security. Use ONLY in /api serverless functions. Never ship to the browser.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-supabase-service-role-key

# [public]  Anon (publishable) key. Safe for the browser; respects RLS.
# (If used in frontend code, re-expose it with a VITE_ prefix on purpose.)
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key

# ── Token encryption ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [server-only]  AES-256-GCM key used by /lib/crypto.ts to encrypt WHOOP
# tokens before storing them in Supabase. Must decode to exactly 32 bytes.
# Generate one with:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=base64-encoded-32-byte-key

# ── Scheduled sync ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [server-only]  Shared secret proving a request to /api/sync came from Vercel
# Cron and not the open internet. NOT a key — api/sync.ts compares it
# byte-for-byte with timingSafeEqual and never decodes it, so any sufficiently
# random string works. Generate a value DISTINCT from TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
#
# In Vercel, scope this to PRODUCTION ONLY (cron does not run on preview).
# Vercel then injects `Authorization: Bearer $CRON_SECRET` automatically.
#
# NOT required for local dev: scripts/sync-whoop.mjs calls syncAll() directly
# and never crosses the HTTP boundary. Only needed if you curl the deployed
# endpoint by hand, or run `vercel dev` and hit /api/sync over HTTP.
#
# WARNING — fails closed and SILENTLY: with this unset, isAuthorized() returns
# 401 before doing any work, so the nightly sync never runs, Supabase stays
# empty, and every chart renders its "no data yet" state with nothing in the
# app logs to explain it. See vercel-env-setup.md (variable 8).
CRON_SECRET=base64-random-string-distinct-from-the-encryption-key
